Dia. 04 4 Points
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par For the same reason like before, we marked the borderlines with Xs. It has to be marked at the same places like before.
\par
\par Black has 10 points, White has 8 points.
\par
\par After counting it is
\par (12-10)+(8-6)=\cf1\b 4 points\cf0\b0 . Therefore Black 1 and 3 in the \b Dia. 01\b0  or White 1 and 3 in \b Dia. 03\b0  are worth 4 points.
\par
\par }
